ic class loading pattern for the public Mockito API, but that might lead to failures. There’s a possibility that the coverage report was generated from the nativeTestCompile agent instead of the JVM. The active call sites suggest that previous tests didn’t cover everything in the \\\"javaTest\\\". The fallback to ReflectionMemberAccessor could explain some issues, but I need to verify all dependencies carefully.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Investigating initialization errors**\\n\\nI’m diving into how the InstrumentationMemberAccessor works. If it catches an error silently during initialization and only throws a `MockitoInitializationException` if `INITIALIZATION_ERROR` isn't null, then that could affect coverage. It seems like the ModuleMemberAccessor will fallback to ReflectionMemberAccessor. I worry that if `ByteBuddyAgent.install` fails due to not being attached in CI, that could be why my tests don’t provide coverage. I need to ensure that the static initialization of InstrumentationMemberAccessor is covered properly, especially if there’s a dynamic loading issue.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Inspecting dynamic access**\\n\\nI'm looking into whether the dynamic report collected during `nativeTestCompile` can provide any insights. It seems that no tests are running at build time. To dig deeper, I’ll check the `build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/reflection-calls` directory to see if it contains any useful information or lines related to this issue. My goal is to uncover the dynamic access details that could help clarify what's happening here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_PKTnZRmdwObnDUUuV72UYdfd|fc_0ede01fd727da590016a21aa247c008193aaf880ca50f1f913", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build/native/nativeTestCompile/dynamic-access/mockito-core-5.0.0/reflection-calls.json", "limit": 40}, "partialJson": "{\"path\":\"tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build/native/n